actona.name: actona

revisions.description: (1) Added aclogSeverity and aclogMsgText objects. (2) deprecated csLogsTrap, esLogsTrap, mgrLogsTrap objects and replaced it with acCsLOgsTrap, acEsLogsTrap, and acMgrLogsTrap objects. (2) deprecated logNotificationsGroup and replaced it with logNotificationsGroupRev1.

esTotalWrittenBytes.name: esTotalWrittenBytes
esTotalWrittenBytes.description: The total number of kilobytes written to the EdgeServer using the CIFS protocol

esRemoteRequestCount.name: esRemoteRequestCount
esRemoteRequestCount.description: The total number of remote synchronous CIFS requests sent to the CoreServer

esLocalRequestCount.name: esLocalRequestCount
esLocalRequestCount.description: The total number of CIFS requests the EdgeServer handled locally or sent asynchronously to the CoreServer

esTotalRemoteTime.name: esTotalRemoteTime
esTotalRemoteTime.description: The total duration of all remote synchronous CIFS requests sent to the CoreServer

esTotalLocalTime.name: esTotalLocalTime
esTotalLocalTime.description: The total duration of all CIFS requests to the EdgeServer (handled either locally or asynchronously)

esConnectedSessionCount.name: esConnectedSessionCount
esConnectedSessionCount.description: The number of currently connected CIFS sessions

esCifsOpenFiles.name: esCifsOpenFiles
esCifsOpenFiles.description: The number of currently open CIFS files

esMaxCacheVolume.name: esMaxCacheVolume
esMaxCacheVolume.description: The maximum disk space (in KB) allocated for data in the EdgeServer cache

esCurrentCacheVolume.name: esCurrentCacheVolume
esCurrentCacheVolume.description: The amount of disk space currently being used for data in the EdgeServer cache

esMaxCacheResources.name: esMaxCacheResources
esMaxCacheResources.description: The maximum number of cache resources (files and directories) supported by the EdgeServer cache, regardless of the size of these resources

esCurrentCacheResources.name: esCurrentCacheResources
esCurrentCacheResources.description: The current number of cache resources (files and directories) held in the EdgeServer cache

esResourceEvictedNum.name: esResourceEvictedNum
esResourceEvictedNum.description: The number of cache resources (files and directories) that have been evicted from the cache since the EdgeServer started

esLastEvictedTime.name: esLastEvictedTime
esLastEvictedTime.description: The time cache resources (files and directories) were last evicted from the EdgeServer cache. 00:00 is displayed if no cache resources have been evicted since the EdgeServer started.

esVolHiWatermark.name: esVolHiWatermark
esVolHiWatermark.description: The disk-usage percentage that triggers the eviction of resources from the EdgeServer cache

esVolLoWatermark.name: esVolLoWatermark
esVolLoWatermark.description: The target disk-usage percentage to be reached via cache eviction when triggered by esVolHiWatermark. When this low watermark is reached, cache eviction stops.

esAmntHiWatermark.name: esAmntHiWatermark
esAmntHiWatermark.description: The percentage of maximum cache resources (defined by esMaxCacheResources) that triggers the eviction of resources from the EdgeServer cache

esAmntLoWatermark.name: esAmntLoWatermark
esAmntLoWatermark.description: The target percetage of total cache resources (defined by esMaxCacheResources) to be reached via cache eviction when triggered by esAmntHiWatermark. When this low watermark is reached, cache eviction stops.

esEvictedAge.name: esEvictedAge
esEvictedAge.description: The amount of time spent in the EdgeServer cache by the resource that was last evicted. If this amount is too short or too long, it is recommended to modify the size of the cache.

esEvictedLastAccess.name: esEvictedLastAccess
esEvictedLastAccess.description: The time when the resource last evicted from the EdgeServer cache was last accessed

esLogsTrap.name: esLogsTrap
esLogsTrap.description: The OID of trap messages related to the EdgeServer. This object is deprecated in favor of acEsLogsTrap.

cfTotalBytesRead.description: Total number of kilobytes read by clients from the Client-side (via cache or remotely) using CIFS AO

cfTotalWrittenBytes.name: cfTotalWrittenBytes
cfTotalWrittenBytes.description: Total number of kilobytes written to the Client-side using the CIFS AO

cfRemoteRequestCount.description: Total number of remote requests processed by CIFS AO

cfLocalRequestCount.name: cfLocalRequestCount
cfLocalRequestCount.description: Total number of local requests processed by CIFS AO

cfTotalRemoteTime.name: cfTotalRemoteTime
cfTotalRemoteTime.description: Total duration of time taken by CIFS AO to process all remote requests

cfTotalLocalTime.name: cfTotalLocalTime
cfTotalLocalTime.description: Total duration of time taken by CIFS AO to process all local requests

cfConnectedSessionCount.name: cfConnectedSessionCount
cfConnectedSessionCount.description: Number of currently connected CIFS sessions

cfCifsOpenFiles.name: cfCifsOpenFiles
cfCifsOpenFiles.description: Number of currently open CIFS files

cfMaxCacheVolume.name: cfMaxCacheVolume
cfMaxCacheVolume.description: Maximum disk space (in KB) allocated for data in the CIFS AO cache

cfCurrentCacheVolume.name: cfCurrentCacheVolume
cfCurrentCacheVolume.description: Amount of disk space currently being used for data in the CIFS AO cache

cfMaxCacheResources.name: cfMaxCacheResources
cfMaxCacheResources.description: Maximum number of cache resources (files and directories) supported by the CIFS AO cache, regardless of the size of these resources

cfCurrentCacheResources.name: cfCurrentCacheResources
cfCurrentCacheResources.description: Current number of cache resources (files and directories) held in the CIFS AO cache

cfResourceEvictedNum.name: cfResourceEvictedNum
cfResourceEvictedNum.description: Number of cache resources (files and directories) that have been evicted from the cache since CIFS AO started

cfLastEvictedTime.name: cfLastEvictedTime
cfLastEvictedTime.description: Time when cache resources (files and directories) were last evicted from the CIFS AO cache. N/A is displayed if no cache resources have been evicted since CIFS AO started

cfVolHiWatermark.name: cfVolHiWatermark
cfVolHiWatermark.description: Disk-usage percentage that triggers the eviction of resources from the CIFS AO cache

cfVolLoWatermark.name: cfVolLoWatermark
cfVolLoWatermark.description: Target disk-usage percentage to be reached via cache eviction when triggered by cfVolHiWatermark. When this low watermark is reached, cache eviction stops

cfAmntHiWatermark.name: cfAmntHiWatermark
cfAmntHiWatermark.description: Percentage of maximum cache resources (defined by cfMaxCacheResources) that triggers the eviction of resources from the CIFS AO cache

cfAmntLoWatermark.name: cfAmntLoWatermark
cfAmntLoWatermark.description: Target percetage of maximum cache resources (defined by cfMaxCacheResources) to be reached via cache eviction when triggered by cfAmntHiWatermark. When this low watermark is reached, cache eviction stops

cfEvictedAge.name: cfEvictedAge
cfEvictedAge.description: Amount of time spent in the CIFS AO cache by the resource that was last evicted. If this amount is too short or too long, it is recommended to modify the size of the cache

cfEvictedLastAccess.name: cfEvictedLastAccess
cfEvictedLastAccess.description: Time when the resource last evicted from the CIFS AO cache was last accessed
